<Content>Great location The Hotel Kapok is in a great location in central Beijing. It is a short walk from the Forbidden City and Tiananmen Square. Further down the road it is in is the city's night food market - complete with deep fried silk worms and crickets. It is also near the Wangfujing shopping area.We paid for the cheapest-rate courtyard room but on arrival were upgraded to a suite. This was fantastic - spacious, huge bath, and included a computer with free internet access.The only niggles are the services. We booked a private trip to the great wall through the hotel's travel booking service, which was very poor. Room service always came with mistakes (the staff answering the phone didn't speak much English). The restaurant's breakfast buffet had a lot of choice but the food wasn't great quality e.g. stale, hard pastries and muffins.But on the whole I would heartily recommend this hotel because of it's great location and nice rooms. 
